<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-01-12T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-01-12T01:00:00-05:00" n="162" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d162">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.2300/19: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-01-12T15:00:00+09:00"><hi rend="italic">January 12,
                                        1924—3 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received January 12—1:55
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>10. Department’s 8, January 10, 5 p.m. Japanese authorities now state
                            they have no objection to visit to Tokyo of an officer to discuss
                            details and technical requirements of flight but as hitherto reported
                            they do object to pathfinding expedition described in Department’s
                            instruction of July 18, 1923, and enclosure from War Department dated
                            July 5, which had been communicated to Foreign Office on August
                            14th.</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>